      • getButtons

        public GUI.Button[] getButtons()
        This method returns an array with all buttons. The index is the correct position of this button. If there is no button the element will be null
        Returns:
        an array of the size of the gui which contains all buttons in the right index or null if there is no button in that index

      • registerButton

        public void registerButton(int slot,
                           java.util.function.Consumer<GUI.ButtonClickEvent> click)
        This method creates a new button on a certain position without changing the design at this position.
        Parameters:
        slot - the slot of this button
        click - the action what will happen when a player clicks on it.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the slot is out of range An example will be GUI.registerButton(0, click -> { TODO: What happen when a player click the button });

      • registerButton

        public void registerButton(int slot,
                           org.bukkit.inventory.ItemStack design,
                           java.util.function.Consumer<GUI.ButtonClickEvent> click)
        This Method creates a new Button in this GUI. The ItemStack represents the design of the button.
        Parameters:
        slot - the slot where the button should be
        item - the ItemStack-Design of the Button
        click - what happens when a player clicks the button
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the design is null or the slot is out of range An example would be registerButton(0, ItemStackAPI.createItemStack(Material.GRASS), click -> { TODO: What happens if the button is clicked });
